snippet.textDisplay:
It is close to 4am where I am rn... I’m really upset over things that happened tonight and a lot of past memories resurfacing. I haven't been dealing with my emotions the best lately, because not so long ago, I had been doing really well. For a long period of time from 2018-2019, I attended counselling sessions which helped me realise a lot of factors about myself and find methods of which I get my thoughts and feelings out like writing, drawing, colouring in, small things like this. Midway through last year, I stopped attending, feeling i Ionger needed to. In the past few weeks, I have lost my ways of dealing with my emotions properly and resorted back to very bad, old habits. So, while sitting up this morning and watching your video Jack, I remembered why I stopped. I don’t want to feel the need to go through that process again. I don’t want my parents worrying about why I think I need to return to counselling when they believe I’ve been doing really well... but this video has really helped me reflect and remember that this isn’t something someone has to do alone.

Your videos, along with other youtubers, have really helped me in moments of needing to cope. You bring a smile to my face and I really appreciate what you do, all the effort you put in and the amount of time and care you dedicate to your craft and your fans. You’ve been a very big stepping stone in the process of me learning grow, by helping me remember the positive perspective while also accepting the negative happens.
I love and support your channel and the community you have built over the years.

Thank you, for being the person you are

snippet.textDisplay: I have episodes of depression, I can be happy at one moment in a day, just to feel like I'm falling apart the next. Talking really does help. Whenever I would try telling my ex-husband, while we were still together, all of my feelings, he would turn it around to himself, and since I'm an empath, I would console him instead. Every single time. It always took a lot out of me, because I felt like no one would listen. My current husband will ask me what's wrong whenever I'm not acting like myself, or as if I'm in one of my dark episodes, and he will sit down and listen, and half the time that's all I need, the other half he knows what to say, and how to say it. He's helped me open up a lot more. My point of this is, if you have someone like my ex-husband in your life, they are not worth it, there are so many better people out there that will actually care. Do not settle, find others that you can freely talk to, it really does help. Sorry for the long 'rant'.
